summary: Dr. Aditya Verma is a Cardiologist and Interventional Cardiologist in Sarat Bose Road, Kolkata and has an experience of 13 years in these fields. Dr. Aditya Verma practices at Calcutta Heart Research Centre in 114B, Sarat Bose Road, Kolkata. He completed MBBS from the Prestigious Armed Forces Medical College, Pune in 2010. Then MD - General Medicine from Medical College and Hospital, Kolkata in 2015 and then DM - Cardiology from IPGME&R and SSKM Hospital, Kolkata in 2019. He has presented cases and papers in various National & International Fora. Services provided by the doctor are: Coronary & Peripheral Angiography and Angioplasty, Permanent Pacemaker Implantation, ICD, CRT Implantation, Baloon Valvuloplasty, Transcatheter Aortic Valve Implantation, Structural Heart Defects intervention including ASD, VSD, and PDA device closure. Complex & Special echocardiography like TEE, DSE.

Dr. Amal Kumar Khan is a Cardiologist (Heart Specialist) currently attached to the Analogy Superspeciality Wing of the Burdwan Medical College and Hospital. He graduated in 1975 from Calcutta National Medical College and went on to obtain an MD in Medicine from Calcutta University and MNAMS (Med.) from the National Board in 1981. He subsequently completed the DM Cardiology super-specialisation from IPGME&R, Kolkata, in the year 1992.  Dr. Amal Kahn worked as RMO cum Clinical Tutor in the Cardiology Department of SSKM Hospital and as Assistant Professor and Associate Professor at Calcutta National Medical College. He then served as a Professor at IPGME&R & SSKM Hospital. Dr. Khan has also held a position of Head of Department of Cardiology of Calcutta Medical School.  Dr. Khan has to his credit several scientific papers published in reputed journals such as Indian Heart Journal, JAPI, and Indian Medical Journal. He is also Research Guide to MD (Medicine) and DM (Cardiology) students. Dr. Khan is an active member of the Cardiological Society of India and has served on the committee, including as National Secretary from 2005-2008.

Dr. Sumanta Chatterjee is a dedicated and hardworking young Interventional Cardiologist in Kolkata. He completed his medical education at Medical College, Kolkata, receiving Gold Medals for his outstanding performance at the MBBS and MD (Medicine) levels, and topping the institution at the DM (Cardiology) superspeciality degree examination. He is performing radial route angiography and angioplasty with special interest in primary angioplasty round the clock in AMRI Hospital, Dhakuria . Dr chatterjee is well versed in FFR OCT and IVUS guided angioplasties, difficult coronary procedures, bifurcation lesions with newer sophisticated gadgets.He is adept in doing pacemaker, ICD,CRT. He has keen interest in treating cardio diabetes segment and preventive cardiology.

summary: Having graduated from Calcutta National Medical College in 1994, I had migrated to UK in 1996, working in the top most University hospitals all over UK. After completion of my Basic Surgical Training in the NHS, I acquired the MRCS degree from he Royal College of Physicians and Surgeons of Glasgow in 2001. Thereafter, I started my intense and extensive surgical training in Adult Cardiac Surgery in the NHS. I had the privilege and honour of working with some of the top most cardiac surgeons in the world. I remain deeply indebted to them. Their support and guidance helped me to achieve the coveted FRCS Intercollegiate Examination in Cardiothoracic Surgery, often considered to be one of the most prestigious jewels in our speciality.

summary: Dr. Rakesh Sarkar is an experienced cardiologist and electrophysiologist associated with BM Birla Heart Hospital. He specializes in managing complex arrhythmia procedures and implementing novel pacing techniques for heart failure and arrhythmia. Dr. Sarkar is an expert in treating Atrial Fibrillation, Atrial Flutter, Ventricular Tachycardia, CRT-D, and conduction system pacing. Dr. Sarkar completed his MD in General Medicine from Bankura Sammilani Medical College and DM in Cardiology from RG Kar Medical College. He further honed his skills with a Post-Doctoral Fellowship in Cardiac Electrophysiology from Care Hospital. Prior to his current role, Dr. Sarkar served as a Consultant Cardiologist and Electrophysiologist at Medanta The Medicity. He has also been an investigator in several significant multicentric trials and has numerous international publications in the fields of pacing and cardiac electrophysiology. Passionate about patient care, Dr. Sarkar is dedicated to providing accurate and high-quality treatment to his patients.
